<C>__{abolofia}
<D>__{you people are wild... wild.}
<A>__{number one backs the blade off. the man raises his napkin to the small wound. a droplet of blood has stained his shirt collar. number one turns around as if to leave. what happens next could be a whim, an after thought. number one spins around and thrusts the blade deep into the man's chest. he withdraws it with a half twist, and in the same motion fatally slashes the translator's throat before the old man's body hits the floor. blood pours from the businessman's mouth onto his scungilli, spreading across the white cloth and onto the floor.}
